######OpenITI#

#META# العنوان: مائة كلمة من كلام أمير المؤمنين عليّ بن أبي طالب عليه السلام
#META# Title (EN): One Hundred Proverbs from the Words of the Commander of the Faithful ʿAlī ibn Abī Ṭālib
#META# المؤلف: الجاحظ
#META# Author: Al-Jāḥiẓ
#META# المحقق: طاهرة قطب الدين
#META# Editor: Tahera Qutbuddin
#META# ISBN: 9780814729144
#META# Publisher: New York University Press
#META# Place of publication: New York
#META# Witness: ا: Istanbul manuscript (early tenth/sixteenth century).Istanbul Topkapi B. 122
#META# Witness: ط: Tokyo manuscript (1158/1745).Tokyo University of Tokyo, Arabic-Daiber collectionms. 136, text no. 2294
#META# Witness: و: al-Waṭwāṭ (d. 578/1182) commentary/versification, edited by M. Heinrich Leberecht Fleischer (Leipzig: W. Vogel Sohn, 1837).
#META# Witness: ب: al-Baḥrānī (d. 679/1280) commentary, edited by Mīr Jalāl al-Dīn al-Ḥusaynī al-Armawī al-Muḥaddith (Qom: Manshūrāt al-Mudarrisīn fī l-Ḥawzah al-ʿIlmiyyah, 1970).
#META# Witness: ث: al-Thaʿālibī (d. 429/1038), al-Iʿjāz wa-l-ījāz, edited by Ibrāhīm Ṣāliḥ (Damascus: Dār al-Bashāʾir, 2001).
#META# Witness: خ: al-Khwārizmī (d. 568/1172), Kitāb al-Manāqib (Najaf: al-Maktabah al-Ḥaydariyyah, 1965).
#META# Editorial declaration: LAL Arabic texts are based upon original manuscript research. For each text, a base manuscript is selected, and notable variants from other consulted manuscripts provided. Details of the manuscripts are provided in the source Desc; the first manuscript listed therein in the base. Arabic ḥarakāt other than shaddah are only provided for disambiguation of possible readings or for unusual words; however all shaddahs except those arising from the assimilation of the definite article are included. Orthography may be standardized to modern style.
#META# Editorial declaration: Texts are divided into numbered sections, which in the bilingual version are used to align the Arabic text with the English translation. The majority of manuscripts will not, of course, have been written with modern paragraph structures: the division of the text into such is for readability and to align with the translation, and is entirely the choice of the editor(s).
#META# Editorial declaration: This edition primarily follows the Istanbul manuscript, supplemented closely by the Tokyo manuscript and Fleischer’s edition of the al-Waṭwāṭ commentary; it also uses al-Armawī’s edition of al-Baḥrānī’s commentary, Ṣāliḥ’s edition of al-Thaʿālibī’s al-Iʿjāz wa-l-ījāz, and the 1965 Najaf edition of al-Khwārizmī’s Kitāb al-Manāqib. With some exceptions, all the sources listed above contain the same hundred sayings, and follow the same order. Within the text of the sayings, there are several minor variants, and a few consequential differences which are noted.
#META# Editorial declaration: The Ibn Durayd-Ibn Abī Ṭāhir preface has been included, using the version provided by the Tokyo manuscript, supplemented by the 1965 Najaf edition of al-Khwārizmī’s Kitāb al-Manāqib.
#META# Editorial declaration: The Istanbul manuscript begins most sayings with “And he also said,” (wa-qāla ayḍan), which does not occur in the other sources; this has also been omitted.
#META# Editorial declaration: The Istanbul manuscript lists only 98 sayings; the missing two (no. 73 and no. 97) have been added from Fleischer’s edition of the al-Waṭwāṭ commentary and collated with the Tokyo manuscript.
#META# Editorial declaration: There are several nouns which are presented in some sources with the definite article al- and in others without (such as no. 15 and no. 16). The Istanbul manuscript has been followed in these; they are not indicated in the variants. 

#META#Header#End#

